&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;YipitData is the leading market research and analytics firm for the disruptive economy. We analyze billions of alternative data points every day to provide accurate, detailed insights across sectors, including e-commerce, ridesharing, payments, and marketplaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our proprietary technology identifies, licenses, cleans, and analyzes third-party data that many of the world’s largest investment funds and corporations depend on. We are backed by The Carlyle Group and Norwest Venture Partners and have been recognized multiple times as one of Inc’s Best Workplaces. Our culture is focused on ownership, mastery, transparency, and impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;YipitData’s product portfolio is underpinned by a growing set of strategic data partnerships. Each partnership acts as a growth driver for the business, unlocking new product development opportunities and expanding our sector coverage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have ~40 active data partnerships and are looking to hire a senior, Director-level individual contributor to scale this motion. This role sits at the intersection of corporate development, strategy, and product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Strategic Data Partnerships, &lt;strong&gt;will identify, evaluate, and execute exclusive, long-cycle data partnerships&lt;/strong&gt; that meaningfully shape our future product direction. This is not a procurement or channel partnerships role. Instead, it requires strong strategic judgment, executive presence, and deep curiosity about how data creates competitive advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In This Role, You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and evaluate potential data partners with high strategic and product value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage directly with CEOs and senior executives — many of whom have not previously monetized their data — to assess opportunity and build alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead discovery and diligence processes to understand data quality, defensibility, and long-term product applicability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic and economic business cases for partnership opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate and execute complex, enterprise-level agreements, including exclusive arrangements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate cross-functionally with legal, product, compliance, engineering, and executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise strong judgment in prioritizing opportunities and determining when to pursue, pause, or walk away&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns partnerships through signature. Ongoing relationship management and renewals are handled by a separate team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signing one flagship, exclusive partnership within the first 12–18 months&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building a repeatable executive-level pipeline of high-quality partnership opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishing clear internal conviction around which opportunities merit investment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Are Likely to Succeed If&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have Director-level (or equivalent) experience in enterprise sales, strategic partnerships, corporate development, investment banking, or strategy consulting with operating exposure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;IC focused, ideal for enterprise sellers looking to transition into a non-traditional sales role and quota attainme

